commitResults.messageBody: Echo commands by user and exit when user types 'bye'.
User input is now added to an item list. 'list' command prints the list.
Task class created. User can mark task in list as done.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add Todo, Event and Deadline Tasks
commitResults.messageBody:
Implements TodoTask, EventTask, DeadlineTask classes as subclasses of Task.

Keying in  'done' without anything after no longer causes an error.

Some wrong user inputs are now handled with try-catch blocks instead of if-else blocks.

Some redundant code removed.

runtest.sh can be used to semi-automate testing.

Added delete function to remove tasks from list.

The number of tasks in list will now be printed whenever a new task is added or removed.
Added save/load feature for itemList. Adjusted some code formatting to match module standards.
Event and Deadline tasks now parse dates input in yyyy-mm-dd format.
fixes bug in EventTask from manual merging of branches.

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor code to include more OOP elements
commitResults.messageBody:
Added Ui, Parser, Storage and TaskList classes.
Refactored Duke class.
Added Command class and subclasses.
Created and moved classes into duke, duke.task and duke.command packages.
added JUnit support and 3 JUnit test methods.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add JavaDoc documentation to several methods
Update code to match module standard

commitResults.messageBody: Added ability to find tasks using the 'find' command.

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix import statement issues in Parser

commitResults.messageBody: Added basic GUI to Duke, removed text-based UI.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add custom exceptions and make dialog box resizeable
commitResults.messageBody:
Many exceptions are similar.
Let's create custom DukeExceptions so they can be grouped together.

Dialog boxes are a fixed size.
Dialog is cut off beyond a certain point.
Let's make them resizeable according to the message length.

commitResults.messageTitle: Make exiting the program less abrupt
commitResults.messageBody:
Using the 'bye' command would immediately close Duke without an exit message.
This can seem too abrupt.
Let's create an exit message after the 'bye' command and close Duke after the user acknowledges the message.
